  <pre slot=3D"code">    function sum(n) {
      let total =3D 0;
      for (let i =3D 1; i &lt;=3D n; i++) {
        total +=3D i;
      }
      return total;
    }
    sum(1e9);
  </pre>
</s-code-timer>
<p>On my laptop this takes just under 1 second. The time you get may be dif=
ferent,
and it may vary by a few tens of milliseconds each time you run it. This is
expected.</p>
<p>Timing code this way, by taking the start time and the end time and find=
ing the
difference, is called <b>wall-clock time</b>.</p>
<p>How long do you think 2 billion, <code>2e9</code>, will take?</p>
