  The relationship between a function's input and how long it takes to exec=
ute
  is called its <b>time complexity</b>, and <b>big O notation</b> is how we
  communicate what the time complexity of a function is.
</s-dog>
<p>Play around with the buttons below. Each bar adds an extra 1 billion to =
the <code>n</code>
that we pass to <code>sum</code>, so the <h- key=3D"run">1e9</h-> button ca=
lls <code>sum(1e9)</code>,
the <h- key=3D"run">2e9</h-> button calls <code>sum(2e9)</code>, and so on.=
 You should see
<code>2e9</code> take about twice as long as <code>1e9</code>, and <code>3e=
9</code> take about three times as
long as <code>1e9</code>.</p>
